cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper discusses wideband spectrum sensing algorithms for cognitive radio networks, which involves signal processing, information theory, and network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
